reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for a 2 week trip. I do not like to check in bags. This was the perfect size! Fit all of my travel items and then some. The material of this bag is excellent. Wheels roll perfectly and was able to move around with ease. I am very satisfied with this purchase.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars very sturdy and i like the lock feature
reviews.reviewText: pretty good suitcase for the case. fits a lot of clothes and the lock feature is really nice and easy to figure out

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My daughter travels often and needed a solid piece of luggage that was affordable. We found it. This bag has already made several trips and performed well. It is clean looking and looks exactly like more high priced luggage. Way better than expected. We are already planning on buying more pieces.

reviews.reviewText: I have not yet traveled with this suit case. I comppared it to some of the other suitcases I own and it is lighter and the wheels swivel and roll smoothly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Smooth rolling on spinners
reviews.reviewText: This is a good size suitcase for carry-on, it is hard sided, so it is durable. It is fairly lightweight, rolls easily. I think they are quality spinners They are rolling nice and smooth. The bag has a nice appearance, but I wish I would have gotten a bright color instead of generic black, must put some stickers on it to make it stand out!

reviews.reviewText: I like the actual color better than that in the pictures. The design is concise and beautiful, which is what I'm looking for. Big double wheels at each corner, making it sturdy and easy to maneuver. Love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great purchase. Easy to maneuver, light weight and affordable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Some issues but I stil use ir
reviews.reviewText: I do love,spinner wheels they really make a big difference. This bag looks good and seems tough enough. I like that it’s 22” and not 20”. I tend to overpack so I need the space. The handle is a little shaky though and I like to carry my tote strapped over the handle so that somewhat concerning. I do like how it’s divided inside and has all the dividers to keep things neat. Unfortunate though that it doesn’t expand and doesn’t have the front pocket that some hardshells do now

reviews.reviewTitle: There is no side handle on the 20” version
reviews.reviewText: While I am generally really happy with the case, I realised there was no side handle on the case despite it shown in the main images. This was one of my must haves for a carry on case, so may end up sending this back. A shame as it is a really nice case - seams/stitching covered; holds its shape when empty; nice sturdy wheels, top handle sits fairly flush, good space inside. The pull up handle doesnt slide as easily as I’d like but seems fairly sturdy otherwise. Decription for the smaller siz needs to clearly indicate it does not have a side handle.
